  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>VATS hyperthermic pleural chemoperfusion</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Active Comparator</arm_group_type>
    <description>The patients undergo a VATS drainage of pleural effusion with adhesiolysis and complete mobilization of the lung, following by a 1 hour hyperthermic (40oC)chemoperfusion by means of a pump machine.</description>
  </arm_group>
  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>Bedside talc slurry pleurodesis</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Active Comparator</arm_group_type>
    <description>The patients undergo tube thoracostomy under local anesthesia. When the lung is fully expanded, talc slurry bed-side pleurodesis is performed.</description>
  </arm_group>
